                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Pak visa norm relief 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	New Delhi, June 10: The Centre has proposed relaxing norms for extending long-term visas to Pakistanis with Indian connections.         
	The proposal comes days before home minister P. Chidambarams visit to Pakistan for the Saarc summit of interior ministers.         
	The relaxation is for Pakistans minority communities  Sikhs and Hindus  Pakistani women married to Indians and staying here, Indian women married to Pakistanis and returning either after a divorce or the husbands death.        
	It is applicable to women who do not have male relatives in Pakistan or cases involving extreme compassion. The Centre is also considering extension of visas to Pakistani citizens settled in Kerala.                                                                                                                                                           
